1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,198
<The dream that caused Mio's mother to fall to her death>

2
00:00:07,198 --> 00:00:12,165
<Mio deepens his forbidden friendship with Yume without realizing it>

3
00:00:13,165 --> 00:00:16,759
(Yume) Sorry (Mio) Thank you for that.

4
00:00:16,759 --> 00:00:20,198
< Unable to bear the guilt, he confessed everything in a letter.

5
00:00:20,198 --> 00:00:23,363
Yume turned herself in to the police, but

6
00:00:23,363 --> 00:00:27,165
It wasn't Mio who read the letter...>

7
00:00:31,330 --> 00:00:34,561
(Manager) Just make sure everything is shiny.

8
00:00:34,561 --> 00:00:37,726
I'm glad! The ending seems a little high.

9
00:00:37,726 --> 00:00:40,594
I'm happy, I'm happy

10
00:00:40,594 --> 00:00:43,858
(Manager) Perfect. Also, sorry for the name tag.

11
00:00:43,858 --> 00:00:47,528
It will arrive tomorrow, so please

12
00:00:48,528 --> 00:00:54,495
(Manager) But that's it, Yume is a nice name.

13
00:00:54,495 --> 00:00:56,726
Ah, that's it!

14
00:00:56,726 --> 00:01:00,330
(Manager) Mom? father? Huh?

15
00:01:00,330 --> 00:01:04,396
(Manager) No, I hope you can have big dreams.

16
00:01:04,396 --> 00:01:07,462
Did you put it on? Which one?

17
00:01:07,462 --> 00:01:10,330
I wish it was a dream

18
00:01:10,330 --> 00:01:14,693
(Manager) What? Is it okay to laugh at that?

19
00:01:14,693 --> 00:01:18,462
Huh? Wait a minute... Eh! Huh?

20
00:01:18,462 --> 00:01:20,264
What's inside this?

21
00:01:20,264 --> 00:01:23,264
Ah, the smell of throwing it away was quite strong.

22
00:01:23,264 --> 00:01:27,858
No, no, no, no! This is sauce! Mine!

23
00:01:27,858 --> 00:01:32,000
58 years since our founding!

24
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:37,594
What should I do... ah... eh?

25
00:01:37,594 --> 00:01:41,726
♬〜

26
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:43,792
(Manager) Hey!

27
00:01:43,792 --> 00:01:57,429
♬〜

28
00:02:00,891 --> 00:02:09,627
♬〜

29
00:02:09,627 --> 00:02:17,429
(cell phone vibration sound)

30
00:02:18,924 --> 00:02:24,759
Mio-chan, I'm sorry... 📱Where are you now?

31
00:02:26,891 --> 00:02:32,594
Have you read it? 📱Police! Taro-kun was just taken away.

32
00:02:32,594 --> 00:02:36,000
Huh? You stole money

33
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,792
From your mother's cram school

34
00:02:38,792 --> 00:02:45,561
📱Who? That's why Taro and your mother came too.

35
00:02:45,561 --> 00:02:49,825
Mom? So what about Taro?

36
00:02:49,825 --> 00:02:53,825
📱So the police took you there? Where are you now?

37
00:02:53,825 --> 00:02:57,297
📱Taro-kun, I keep calling you

38
00:02:57,297 --> 00:03:04,231
Mio-chan… Have you read it? So what?

39
00:03:04,231 --> 00:03:08,396
📱 Where are you now?

40
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:12,198
(No sound) Huh?

41
00:03:12,198 --> 00:03:14,363
(clicks tongue)

42
00:03:23,330 --> 00:03:28,528
(Sakuma) Yume... Why is this...

43
00:03:28,528 --> 00:03:30,957
(Sakura) That woman killed that person.

44
00:03:30,957 --> 00:03:33,363
Does that mean you messed up with your dad too?

45
00:03:33,363 --> 00:03:37,330
No, I wasn't trying to help...

46
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:43,297
Huh? a little bit…

47
00:03:43,297 --> 00:03:46,429
What about him? No, that's why the police are coming now.

48
00:03:46,429 --> 00:03:53,165
Huh? That woman... What? Women are different, Taro-kun.

49
00:03:53,165 --> 00:03:56,264
Did you get 1 million?

50
00:03:56,264 --> 00:03:59,825
Did you ask? Huh? That can't be true!

51
00:03:59,825 --> 00:04:02,165
Sorry, sorry, sorry... I didn't mean it that way...

52
00:04:02,165 --> 00:04:06,858
What exceeded the capacity?

53
00:04:06,858 --> 00:04:09,231
Huh? Oh wait!

54
00:04:09,231 --> 00:04:11,429
Oh, hey, what's going on?

55
00:04:11,429 --> 00:04:14,198
I mean, don't you know Yume?

56
00:04:14,198 --> 00:04:19,132
Did you hear? Huh? What?

57
00:04:19,132 --> 00:04:24,660
Oh wait! Why is everyone leaving silently?

58
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:31,330
♬〜

59
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:33,528
Sister?

60
00:04:33,528 --> 00:04:44,858
♬〜

61
00:04:44,858 --> 00:04:47,231
(Jimbo) This one million yen came from my mother's cram school.

62
00:04:47,231 --> 00:04:49,462
You stole it, right?

63
00:04:49,462 --> 00:04:54,462
♬〜

64
00:04:54,462 --> 00:04:58,561
This kind of soap really stinks.

65
00:05:01,561 --> 00:05:05,330
Did you know? I don't know

66
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:09,858
Then why were you in front of the police?

67
00:05:09,858 --> 00:05:14,099
If I knew that kid was the culprit, I wouldn't have called the police.

68
00:05:14,099 --> 00:05:16,825
I don't even know how to look at security cameras.

69
00:05:16,825 --> 00:05:20,198
Mom, I'm embarrassed.

70
00:05:20,198 --> 00:05:23,000
How did you know you were at Mio-chan's place?

71
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,924
Who is Mio-chan? Oh, the house from earlier?

72
00:05:27,924 --> 00:05:32,396
A long time ago... don't you know?

73
00:05:32,396 --> 00:05:36,660
I remember when that girl got angry, I put in the app.

74
00:05:36,660 --> 00:05:39,726
Are you friends? Huh?

75
00:05:39,726 --> 00:05:46,528
Mio-chan? Oh no, it really stinks

76
00:05:46,528 --> 00:05:50,693
What is it? What?

77
00:05:50,693 --> 00:05:55,330
Hi, what happened to you today?

78
00:05:55,330 --> 00:06:00,726
Ah...my younger brother stole 1 million from my mother's cram school.

79
00:06:00,726 --> 00:06:03,165
Huh? No, it's a bit of a mistake...

80
00:06:03,165 --> 00:06:07,594
Well, in a way, it's like revenge.

81
00:06:07,594 --> 00:06:11,363
yes? This person remarried

82
00:06:11,363 --> 00:06:15,660
Ever since I had a child there, I've been ignoring my younger brother.

83
00:06:15,660 --> 00:06:19,594
My brother ended up running away to me.

84
00:06:19,594 --> 00:06:22,792
Is that so? No, it's not.

85
00:06:22,792 --> 00:06:26,561
It's not like that.

86
00:06:26,561 --> 00:06:30,429
Well, excuse me.

87
00:06:34,693 --> 00:06:40,495
(Chihiro) What? You're telling the truth

88
00:06:40,495 --> 00:06:44,396
Why do you know a detective?

89
00:06:45,792 --> 00:06:48,924
If that's the case, please do well.

90
00:06:48,924 --> 00:06:53,297
Humans: When you make a mistake, there are only two ways to deal with it.

91
00:06:53,297 --> 00:06:59,132
You can solve it with money, or you can just ignore it... and get away with it.

92
00:06:59,132 --> 00:07:01,396
Hehehe

93
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:09,198
What, a lie? Is there really something?

94
00:07:09,198 --> 00:07:13,297
Does it have anything to do with Taro taking the money?

95
00:07:13,297 --> 00:07:16,198
So don't say there's nothing!

96
00:07:16,198 --> 00:07:25,693
(cell phone vibration sound)

97
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:36,198
Does Mio have any kind of relationship with anyone?

98
00:07:36,198 --> 00:07:38,198
Huh?

99
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:44,561
It's not like what happened with your father, right?

100
00:07:47,891 --> 00:07:50,891
(Jimbo) Um...

101
00:07:50,891 --> 00:07:53,561
(Chihiro) Really... Thank you for bothering me this time.

102
00:07:53,561 --> 00:07:58,132
I'm sorry, but I admit that I'm sure.

103
00:07:58,132 --> 00:08:00,561
As a problem at home on the part of the mother

104
00:08:00,561 --> 00:08:02,792
Withdraw the complaint... I withdraw it I withdraw it

105
00:08:02,792 --> 00:08:05,066
(Jimbo) If there are any other problems at home...

106
00:08:05,066 --> 00:08:07,660
(Chihiro) Ah, no, there's no need to worry.

107
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:10,561
I'm really sorry

108
00:08:13,264 --> 00:08:16,660
Taro is also sorry.

109
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:20,132
Mom, I don't realize many things.

110
00:08:22,924 --> 00:08:25,429
(Sound of a pat on the back)

111
00:08:39,066 --> 00:08:45,297
(cell phone vibration sound)

112
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:49,429
(Taro) Sister, I'm sorry.

113
00:08:51,693 --> 00:08:54,627
What are you thinking?

114
00:08:56,792 --> 00:09:02,363
Man: Do you have to show it to me?

115
00:09:02,363 --> 00:09:05,429
Because I wanted to help Mr. Kondo.

116
00:09:05,429 --> 00:09:09,528
Besides, if it's with my mom, I guess it's retribution...

117
00:09:09,528 --> 00:09:13,759
No good is no good

118
00:09:13,759 --> 00:09:16,099
sorry

119
00:09:18,330 --> 00:09:21,528
Man: I'll show you...

120
00:09:21,528 --> 00:09:23,924
That's right. I got the money I stole.

121
00:09:23,924 --> 00:09:27,132
There's no woman who makes me nervous

122
00:09:27,132 --> 00:09:32,264
Shut up, steal, lie.

123
00:09:32,264 --> 00:09:36,165
That's not love or kindness or anything.

124
00:09:38,231 --> 00:09:41,066
(Taro) Sorry.

125
00:09:41,066 --> 00:09:44,330
Sister, why were the police there this morning?

126
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:46,495
Huh?

127
00:09:48,957 --> 00:09:51,198
Well, but it was good

128
00:09:51,198 --> 00:09:54,594
My sister wasn't there when the police came.

129
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,594
Me, that house again

130
00:09:57,594 --> 00:10:02,495
I was wondering if I had to go back.

131
00:10:04,759 --> 00:10:11,528
Because that's what I hated the most

132
00:10:14,891 --> 00:10:17,726
(Taro) Sister

133
00:10:19,264 --> 00:10:22,528
Don't disappear suddenly

134
00:10:22,528 --> 00:10:31,627
♬〜

135
00:10:31,627 --> 00:10:36,066
No, I'm not looking for that much...

136
00:10:38,726 --> 00:10:46,132
When you, the police came, Mio-chan...

137
00:10:46,132 --> 00:10:48,264
Huh?

138
00:10:48,264 --> 00:10:54,429
♬〜

139
00:10:54,429 --> 00:11:01,099
I promise my sister won't disappear.

140
00:11:01,099 --> 00:11:06,165
♬〜

141
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:09,363
No, wait, this is good after all.

142
00:11:09,363 --> 00:11:13,165
It's embarrassing. It's embarrassing because we're siblings.

143
00:11:13,165 --> 00:11:14,825
No, they're siblings, but I get it.Okay, then...

144
00:11:14,825 --> 00:11:17,528
Okay, then I don't want to cross my arms anymore. It's a wedding.

145
00:11:17,528 --> 00:11:19,957
Hahahaha a little...

146
00:11:19,957 --> 00:11:22,825
Eh, Mr. Kondo?

147
00:11:25,594 --> 00:11:28,396
I read it though

148
00:11:30,627 --> 00:11:33,297
what? that

149
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:37,924
What about Mio-chan? Because I found it first

150
00:11:37,924 --> 00:11:41,528
That person doesn't know yet

151
00:11:41,528 --> 00:11:45,198
What are you talking about? So your sister is a criminal...

152
00:11:45,198 --> 00:11:47,660
different! different!

153
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:53,330
(Sakura) Don't touch me! Seriously, don't be silly!

154
00:11:53,330 --> 00:11:56,396
what? A criminal is...

155
00:11:56,396 --> 00:11:59,462
(Sakura) Don't tell me yourself. I wrote a letter and sent it out.

156
00:11:59,462 --> 00:12:02,198
It was all planned out, right?

157
00:12:02,198 --> 00:12:04,891
What about the police? Haven't you gone yet?

158
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:09,825
Please wait just one day

159
00:12:13,495 --> 00:12:19,495
It was all your fault.

160
00:12:20,858 --> 00:12:23,066
(Sakura) If you don't tell me by tomorrow

161
00:12:23,066 --> 00:12:26,099
I'll do all the talking

162
00:12:26,099 --> 00:12:36,594
♬〜

163
00:12:36,594 --> 00:12:38,858
What do you mean?

164
00:12:38,858 --> 00:12:43,429
♬〜

165
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:46,396
Huh? So does that mean Yume came too?

166
00:12:46,396 --> 00:12:52,297
Yes, you went home with Taro a while ago.

167
00:12:52,297 --> 00:12:59,000
1 million, what's the motive... No, I don't know the details either.

168
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:02,297
I'm sorry, but thank you very much

169
00:13:02,297 --> 00:13:04,462
(Endo) No.

170
00:13:04,462 --> 00:13:11,000
♬〜

171
00:13:12,429 --> 00:13:15,858
OK? Ah, sorry

172
00:13:15,858 --> 00:13:19,627
I have some strength to stand...

173
00:13:25,528 --> 00:13:31,462
I'm sorry about everything, eh?

174
00:13:31,462 --> 00:13:36,033
A lot of things about your mother...

175
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:39,099
It seems like I've made it more confusing.

176
00:13:39,099 --> 00:13:43,363
Ah, no, that's not it at all...

177
00:13:43,363 --> 00:13:48,165
In fact, thank you for investigating this properly.

178
00:13:48,165 --> 00:13:52,099
I am grateful to Mr. Endo.

179
00:13:54,363 --> 00:13:58,825
Ah, phone... Huh?

180
00:13:58,825 --> 00:14:04,495
Oh, did you make a sound? Sorry

181
00:14:04,495 --> 00:14:09,495
I have to call Mr. Kondo about compensation.

182
00:14:09,495 --> 00:14:14,825
In the end, you can't pay... It's a bad call, isn't it?

183
00:14:14,825 --> 00:14:17,165
ah…

184
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:23,561
Maybe it was my fault after all.

185
00:14:28,165 --> 00:14:31,891
Okay

186
00:14:31,891 --> 00:14:37,198
I stand up and walk home

187
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,924
actually…

188
00:14:44,957 --> 00:14:48,594
My wife also committed suicide.

189
00:14:48,594 --> 00:14:50,264
Huh?

190
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:54,561
(Endo) It's been 10 years already.

191
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:58,528
I still don't know why

192
00:14:58,528 --> 00:15:04,033
I had no idea that I was thinking that way.

193
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:09,825
No, I wasn't trying to notice.

194
00:15:09,825 --> 00:15:13,792
I blamed myself a lot.

195
00:15:17,726 --> 00:15:21,495
This is not as a criminal.

196
00:15:21,495 --> 00:15:27,693
As someone who also lost a family member...

197
00:15:30,264 --> 00:15:35,726
When I stopped chasing the reason

198
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:40,297
I felt like I was finally able to accept my wife's death.

199
00:15:45,792 --> 00:15:47,462
(knock) Sister!

200
00:15:47,462 --> 00:15:53,726
Sister, please explain! Open it! Sister...

201
00:15:55,792 --> 00:15:57,726
My sister has somewhere to go.

202
00:15:57,726 --> 00:16:01,198
(Taro) That's not an answer.

203
00:16:01,198 --> 00:16:04,594
What is a criminal?

204
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:08,792
I have to go anyway, so go away

205
00:16:08,792 --> 00:16:10,792
(sound of falling)

206
00:16:10,792 --> 00:16:14,792
Sorry... are you okay?

207
00:16:14,792 --> 00:16:19,792
♬〜

208
00:16:19,792 --> 00:16:25,792
I'll tell you everything when I get back.

209
00:16:25,792 --> 00:16:38,297
♬〜

210
00:16:38,297 --> 00:16:40,693
Dream!

211
00:16:42,726 --> 00:16:46,759
What does that letter mean?

212
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:49,759
So you went to the police?

213
00:16:49,759 --> 00:17:04,297
♬〜

214
00:17:04,297 --> 00:17:06,528
Wait a minute!

215
00:17:06,528 --> 00:17:09,561
So I'm going to tell Mio-chan everything now.

216
00:17:09,561 --> 00:17:14,132
And to Taro... I'll go to the police after that.

217
00:17:14,132 --> 00:17:16,561
No, but even if such a decision was suddenly made by one person...

218
00:17:16,561 --> 00:17:20,297
Didn't I say earlier that it's impossible to do both?

219
00:17:22,231 --> 00:17:25,693
I don't want to lie to Mio-chan anymore

220
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:31,594
Because I'm hungry

221
00:17:33,132 --> 00:17:37,957
I'll contact you after I tell Mio-chan everything, so keep that in mind.

222
00:17:39,891 --> 00:17:42,297
What about you, Taro?

223
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:46,495
What should we do?

224
00:17:54,594 --> 00:17:58,594
♬(Music playing from the speaker)

225
00:17:58,594 --> 00:18:04,198
♬〜

226
00:18:04,198 --> 00:18:06,396
Mio-chan? ♬(Music playing from the speaker)

227
00:18:06,396 --> 00:18:08,924
Mio-chan? ♬(Music playing from the speaker)

228
00:18:08,924 --> 00:18:11,594
Mio-chan! Oh! Huh?

229
00:18:11,594 --> 00:18:15,462
What are you doing? I mean, why aren't you answering the phone?

230
00:18:15,462 --> 00:18:18,363
What are you doing?

231
00:18:21,132 --> 00:18:27,561
Even if we talk about this tomorrow...

232
00:18:27,561 --> 00:18:32,231
I can't go tomorrow and pay compensation.

233
00:18:32,231 --> 00:18:35,165
I'm giving up my inheritance

234
00:18:35,165 --> 00:18:38,264
Tomorrow, when it's decided

235
00:18:38,264 --> 00:18:42,264
This house and the memories I have with my mother.

236
00:18:42,264 --> 00:18:46,462
That I have to let go of everything

237
00:18:48,297 --> 00:18:51,132
Tomorrow... Yes, tomorrow

238
00:18:51,132 --> 00:18:55,132
There is a time limit for disinheriting, so even now it's pretty close.

239
00:18:55,132 --> 00:19:00,561
So tomorrow, I ran away to drink.

240
00:19:05,132 --> 00:19:06,792
That's Mio-chan

241
00:19:06,792 --> 00:19:11,099
What about you, Taro? Was it okay?

242
00:19:11,099 --> 00:19:13,165
When I went to the police, they said you went home with me.

243
00:19:13,165 --> 00:19:19,594
That's what I've been told. It's okay now.

244
00:19:19,594 --> 00:19:22,726
Sorry for bothering you

245
00:19:24,264 --> 00:19:30,462
Taro-kun, you saved 1 million for that girl, right?

246
00:19:30,462 --> 00:19:35,726
I guess I was somehow involved indirectly.

247
00:19:35,726 --> 00:19:41,792
Turning pure love into a crime? Please apologize

248
00:19:41,792 --> 00:19:45,528
Isn't that wrong?

249
00:19:45,528 --> 00:19:49,858
I mean, where did you go this morning?

250
00:19:49,858 --> 00:19:52,693
it is…

251
00:20:02,957 --> 00:20:07,594
It feels heavy, isn't it?

252
00:20:07,594 --> 00:20:10,957
I think it's bad, but I can't pay for it.

253
00:20:10,957 --> 00:20:13,792
I'm sorry...

254
00:20:13,792 --> 00:20:16,792
With someone who may end up in a wheelchair for the rest of their lives

255
00:20:16,792 --> 00:20:23,099
Can you tell that family?

256
00:20:23,099 --> 00:20:29,363
Mio-chan, listen to me.

257
00:20:29,363 --> 00:20:34,264
How do you decide? Huh?

258
00:20:34,264 --> 00:20:37,957
Kenken question Ah, do you want to hit me once?

259
00:20:37,957 --> 00:20:42,396
Hey hey... what is that? It's like pouring water on me

260
00:20:42,396 --> 00:20:44,792
It's like a drama... Mio-chan, you know...

261
00:20:44,792 --> 00:20:49,594
Let me talk about whatever it is

262
00:20:49,594 --> 00:20:52,198
Are you worried about me?

263
00:20:52,198 --> 00:20:56,726
It's been showing on my face for a while now, so thank you.

264
00:20:56,726 --> 00:21:01,495
But I can't help it anymore

265
00:21:01,495 --> 00:21:05,792
My heart is finally catching up little by little

266
00:21:05,792 --> 00:21:12,495
I don't know why, but my mother died by herself.

267
00:21:14,462 --> 00:21:20,099
I'm sorry to be the subject of your affair story, but...

268
00:21:20,099 --> 00:21:22,693
please

269
00:21:22,693 --> 00:21:28,726
♬〜

270
00:21:28,726 --> 00:21:30,726
yes

271
00:21:34,132 --> 00:21:37,429
cheers

272
00:21:38,429 --> 00:21:44,429
≪I'm so sorry, Mio-chan≫

273
00:21:44,429 --> 00:21:47,429
≪To tell you the truth

274
00:21:47,429 --> 00:21:52,660
At first, I put the suicide note in the mailbox and returned it.

275
00:21:52,660 --> 00:21:55,561
I'll never see you again

276
00:21:55,561 --> 00:21:57,231
(cell phone vibration sound)

277
00:21:57,231 --> 00:22:02,891
≪I was thinking of ending it all≫

278
00:22:02,891 --> 00:22:09,066
≪I actually talked to Misato-san on the rooftop that day.

279
00:22:09,066 --> 00:22:13,627
In the end, I pushed him on the back and let him die.

280
00:22:13,627 --> 00:22:20,462
As a result, I ended up involving unrelated people.

281
00:22:20,462 --> 00:22:27,891
I was thinking of pretending it all never happened.

282
00:22:27,891 --> 00:22:31,363
≪No matter what I do, I can't take it back.

283
00:22:31,363 --> 00:22:34,231
Because I thought≫

284
00:22:34,231 --> 00:22:42,429
≪However, as I met and talked with you and spent time with you,

285
00:22:42,429 --> 00:22:47,429
I started to like you more and more≫

286
00:22:50,066 --> 00:22:56,297
<<That's why I have to tell you the truth>>

287
00:22:56,297 --> 00:22:59,957
≪I've come to think so.

288
00:22:59,957 --> 00:23:05,693
In the end, I couldn't say it.

289
00:23:05,693 --> 00:23:15,033
♬〜

290
00:23:15,033 --> 00:23:20,099
A love letter? I wish it was (Sakura)

291
00:23:21,099 --> 00:23:27,198
I'm sorry for making Sacchan feel so bad.

292
00:23:27,198 --> 00:23:31,099
Why did you stop getting divorced?

293
00:23:31,099 --> 00:23:33,330
Huh? (Sakura) Mama that day

294
00:23:33,330 --> 00:23:35,561
If we don't talk about divorce

295
00:23:35,561 --> 00:23:42,066
We didn't get into a fight and my dad didn't leave the house...

296
00:23:42,066 --> 00:23:45,000
Don't you divorce because you think it's your fault?

297
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,132
(Sae) Done

298
00:23:49,165 --> 00:23:54,759
I've never thought about getting divorced.

299
00:23:56,594 --> 00:24:02,825
Why do all adults pretend to be fine and lie?

300
00:24:11,660 --> 00:24:18,429
Hmm... sorry, did you fall asleep?

301
00:24:18,429 --> 00:24:20,594
Yeah

302
00:24:27,957 --> 00:24:31,099
Mio-chan...

303
00:24:31,099 --> 00:24:35,231
There's something I'd like you to ask me.

304
00:24:35,231 --> 00:24:37,561
what?

305
00:24:39,627 --> 00:24:43,198
About your mother

306
00:24:43,198 --> 00:24:47,363
I met you that day

307
00:24:47,363 --> 00:24:51,165
I told you before

308
00:24:51,165 --> 00:24:53,957
In front of the station during the day

309
00:24:55,759 --> 00:25:00,627
Yes, I heard that.

310
00:25:03,264 --> 00:25:11,297
At that time... that...

311
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:18,627
Actually after that...

312
00:25:26,132 --> 00:25:29,462
(sob)

313
00:25:31,396 --> 00:25:35,495
I…

314
00:25:35,495 --> 00:25:39,693
I pushed my back

315
00:25:39,693 --> 00:25:42,033
on the roof

316
00:25:45,561 --> 00:25:50,462
It's not intentional

317
00:25:50,462 --> 00:25:53,297
but…

318
00:25:56,528 --> 00:26:01,660
It's my fault, Mio-chan's mother...

319
00:26:08,627 --> 00:26:12,132
Mio-chan?

320
00:26:16,528 --> 00:26:23,099
♬〜

321
00:26:23,099 --> 00:26:26,627
(sob)

322
00:26:26,627 --> 00:26:33,693
♬〜

323
00:26:33,693 --> 00:26:37,660
(cell phone vibration sound)

324
00:26:37,660 --> 00:26:41,099
Sorry, I was trying to call you now.

325
00:26:41,099 --> 00:26:44,759
(Taro) Aren't you coming back?

326
00:26:44,759 --> 00:26:49,297
Sorry... but tomorrow...

327
00:26:49,297 --> 00:26:52,396
📱(Taro) Enough is enough.

328
00:26:52,396 --> 00:26:59,858
I thought my sister wouldn't lie.

329
00:26:59,858 --> 00:27:03,561
Taro... (no sound)

330
00:27:03,561 --> 00:27:23,561
♬〜

331
00:27:23,561 --> 00:27:25,726
♬〜

332
00:27:25,726 --> 00:27:28,033
Huh? Eh, why are you here?

333
00:27:28,033 --> 00:27:32,297
Ah, I see...

334
00:27:32,297 --> 00:27:34,396
Mio-chan...

335
00:27:34,396 --> 00:27:41,099
Oh, hey, are you off today? Huh?

336
00:27:42,924 --> 00:27:49,000
Would you like to come with me? to the hospital

337
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:12,792
Hey, are you okay?

338
00:28:12,792 --> 00:28:14,462
Yeah

339
00:28:21,627 --> 00:28:27,462
Ah, you and your mom were on the roof.

340
00:28:27,462 --> 00:28:29,825
Huh?

341
00:28:29,825 --> 00:28:36,594
I guess it means that the two people I dreamed about yesterday are my allies.

342
00:28:36,594 --> 00:28:42,198
Mio-chan... It's okay, I'm hungry.

343
00:28:42,198 --> 00:28:45,924
Huh? Wait for me

344
00:28:45,924 --> 00:28:53,132
When it's over, I'll have a dream and drink, and I can go on.

345
00:29:05,132 --> 00:29:07,231
No...

346
00:29:09,198 --> 00:29:10,858
No...

347
00:29:10,858 --> 00:29:22,594
♬〜

348
00:29:22,594 --> 00:29:26,561
(Todoroki) I will continue to pay the full amount for the treatment.

349
00:29:26,561 --> 00:29:30,165
As compensation for damages cannot be paid

350
00:29:30,165 --> 00:29:34,099
There was a request to renounce inheritance.

351
00:29:34,099 --> 00:29:41,066
♬〜

352
00:29:41,066 --> 00:29:45,429
I'm really sorry

353
00:29:47,495 --> 00:29:50,891
(Sakura) Wait a minute, I have an objection.

354
00:29:50,891 --> 00:29:54,726
Everyone doesn't know the truth

355
00:29:54,726 --> 00:30:02,495
(Sae) What? What's the truth? (cell phone vibrating sound)

356
00:30:02,495 --> 00:30:04,957
(Sae) Turn off the power.

357
00:30:08,033 --> 00:30:11,759
Um... is that okay?

358
00:30:11,759 --> 00:30:13,429
(Sae) Yes?

359
00:30:16,297 --> 00:30:23,957
That day, I had actually promised to meet my mother.

360
00:30:23,957 --> 00:30:26,264
Huh?

361
00:30:26,264 --> 00:30:30,000
Let's have some food once in a while

362
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:37,330
But in the end I declined, saying I was a little busy.

363
00:30:37,330 --> 00:30:44,561
Actually, it wasn't busy at all, but it was kind of tedious...

364
00:30:44,561 --> 00:30:47,198
Let's do it again next time

365
00:30:48,825 --> 00:30:56,891
If I had met my mother as promised

366
00:30:56,891 --> 00:31:01,198
From that day and that place

367
00:31:01,198 --> 00:31:03,099
My mother never jumped.

368
00:31:03,099 --> 00:31:05,099
(Sakura) No, but that's not the case...

369
00:31:05,099 --> 00:31:10,066
If I hadn't canceled that morning...

370
00:31:12,132 --> 00:31:17,792
I intend to carry that burden forever.

371
00:31:17,792 --> 00:31:22,000
(Sae) What time is it? current

372
00:31:24,363 --> 00:31:28,957
Isn't it amazing that you told me everything honestly? You look like

373
00:31:28,957 --> 00:31:31,957
You just want to feel refreshed, right?

374
00:31:31,957 --> 00:31:36,132
That's just hypocrisy

375
00:31:36,132 --> 00:31:42,297
If you're going to carry me on your back, please heal this person's leg!

376
00:31:42,297 --> 00:31:45,495
Please return it to my messed-up home!

377
00:31:45,495 --> 00:31:48,033
I'm really sorry

378
00:31:48,033 --> 00:31:53,660
I love you. If nothing like this had happened to this person...

379
00:31:53,660 --> 00:31:55,825
Sakura?

380
00:31:55,825 --> 00:31:57,495
Huh?

381
00:31:57,495 --> 00:32:01,495
What is the truth that everyone still doesn't know?

382
00:32:02,660 --> 00:32:13,264
♬〜

383
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:15,330
(sound of door opening)

384
00:32:15,330 --> 00:32:34,000
♬〜

385
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,660
♬〜

386
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:37,561
Mio-chan?

387
00:32:37,561 --> 00:32:48,561
♬〜

388
00:32:56,528 --> 00:33:00,000
Let's have a drink

389
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,825
Hey, wait a minute, wait

390
00:33:08,825 --> 00:33:13,198
Do you still drink? Hmm... I mean, drink...

391
00:33:13,198 --> 00:33:16,528
Oh itai?

392
00:33:17,726 --> 00:33:22,165
I'm sorry, but I think we should settle this.

393
00:33:24,627 --> 00:33:26,924
Hey, adultery!

394
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:33,198
Sorry for calling you so suddenly.

395
00:33:38,165 --> 00:33:42,825
Well, we talked while standing... Once we got to the store...

396
00:33:42,825 --> 00:33:46,594
Ah, is it okay over there? Eh...

397
00:33:46,594 --> 00:33:51,957
(Manager) Thank you! I'll get some water.

398
00:33:54,957 --> 00:33:57,858
What do you mean? I don't have time now

399
00:33:57,858 --> 00:33:59,891
I've been waiting since yesterday, but I haven't heard from you at all.

400
00:33:59,891 --> 00:34:03,363
I was wondering what was going on, and then I got a call from that person...

401
00:34:03,363 --> 00:34:05,594
I don't have time to explain right now.

402
00:34:05,594 --> 00:34:10,198
After all, you didn't say that, right?

403
00:34:10,198 --> 00:34:12,660
Since you couldn't say it, you should leave.

404
00:34:12,660 --> 00:34:15,297
You said the other day that you were hungry.

405
00:34:15,297 --> 00:34:18,033
If you can't tell me the truth, we can't be friends anymore...

406
00:34:18,033 --> 00:34:20,363
Is it no good? Huh?

407
00:34:20,363 --> 00:34:24,297
Sorry to have kept you waiting. Here's some water.

408
00:34:25,594 --> 00:34:28,363
What happened? Yes, sorry to have kept you waiting!

409
00:34:28,363 --> 00:34:30,825
One bottle of beer is fine.

410
00:34:30,825 --> 00:34:33,429
Thank you for your hard work! (Salesperson) Thank you for your hard work!

411
00:34:33,429 --> 00:34:37,165
Excuse me, “Excuse me”… Hehe, yes.

412
00:34:38,363 --> 00:34:41,594
Um, Mr. Osako...wait a minute.

413
00:34:46,330 --> 00:34:48,759
What happened to your wife?

414
00:34:48,759 --> 00:34:52,759
Huh? ah…

415
00:34:54,858 --> 00:34:58,033
I'm getting divorced

416
00:34:58,033 --> 00:35:00,231
Huh? Does that mean you got caught?

417
00:35:00,231 --> 00:35:05,429
No, I may have been slightly aware of it.

418
00:35:05,429 --> 00:35:11,561
From myself... I told you everything yesterday.

419
00:35:11,561 --> 00:35:16,891
Everything... everything about infidelity...

420
00:35:20,957 --> 00:35:26,825
Ah, isn't that hypocrisy?

421
00:35:26,825 --> 00:35:33,231
No, the worst part is that you have children, seriously.

422
00:35:33,231 --> 00:35:38,099
What is hypocrisy? Huh? Oh no, today...

423
00:35:38,099 --> 00:35:44,066
Did you even say that earlier?

424
00:35:44,066 --> 00:35:49,231
That... that day

425
00:35:49,231 --> 00:35:53,957
I actually promised to meet your mom.

426
00:35:53,957 --> 00:35:57,396
Let's have dinner sometime

427
00:35:57,396 --> 00:36:03,693
But I refused, right?

428
00:36:03,693 --> 00:36:06,198
I want to talk to my mom face to face.

429
00:36:06,198 --> 00:36:09,924
Hmm...I don't think it's bothersome though.

430
00:36:09,924 --> 00:36:13,693
Now that the shop has closed, I feel lonely at home alone.

431
00:36:13,693 --> 00:36:15,594
If that's what you say

432
00:36:15,594 --> 00:36:20,495
I wonder what I should do... huh?

433
00:36:20,495 --> 00:36:23,099
Caught between such a lazy boss and a cheeky junior.

434
00:36:23,099 --> 00:36:24,759
Selling squid... right?

435
00:36:24,759 --> 00:36:26,726
Somehow, I can't say I'm that happy.

436
00:36:26,726 --> 00:36:29,759
If you feel like you'll get worried if I don't tell you,

437
00:36:29,759 --> 00:36:32,594
Something... hey

438
00:36:33,594 --> 00:36:40,165
But that day, as we had promised, we had dinner together.

439
00:36:40,165 --> 00:36:45,099
Well, just think about it physically?

440
00:36:45,099 --> 00:36:49,594
I don't think my mother would have gone there.

441
00:36:51,066 --> 00:36:55,792
So I'm also responsible for this time.

442
00:36:55,792 --> 00:36:59,066
I talked to that person today.

443
00:36:59,066 --> 00:37:05,231
Then I realized that that's hypocrisy, I just want to feel refreshed.

444
00:37:05,231 --> 00:37:09,033
So I was wondering how Kenken-san was doing.

445
00:37:15,759 --> 00:37:20,660
Well... but I'm sorry, that's not what I mean now.

446
00:37:20,660 --> 00:37:26,660
No, it's you! Look! Everything I want to say

447
00:37:26,660 --> 00:37:28,330
Huh?

448
00:37:33,231 --> 00:37:36,462
Well, it's not good after all. Eh?

449
00:37:36,462 --> 00:37:39,891
Be it a lover, a friend, or even an affair.

450
00:37:39,891 --> 00:37:43,594
Being lied to by the person you love is the worst thing ever.

451
00:37:46,297 --> 00:37:49,231
(Manager) Hello, sorry to have kept you waiting!

452
00:37:49,231 --> 00:37:52,627
Two special ramen noodles

453
00:37:52,627 --> 00:37:55,429
Thank you Wow (Manager) Oh

454
00:37:55,429 --> 00:37:58,396
And one gyoza!

455
00:37:58,396 --> 00:38:02,660
Thank you Yes Yes Wow

456
00:38:05,627 --> 00:38:07,627
That Mr. Osako is actually...

457
00:38:07,627 --> 00:38:10,594
Wow! Damn... Ah...

458
00:38:10,594 --> 00:38:13,594
Hahahahaha

459
00:38:17,924 --> 00:38:21,462
Yeah yeah

460
00:38:21,462 --> 00:38:25,000
Hey, this is really good

461
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:29,594
Huh? Really? what? “Really?” Hehehehe

462
00:38:31,231 --> 00:38:34,000
Wait a minute... Eh, wait, wait...

463
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,429
Hey ramen... eh?

464
00:38:38,165 --> 00:38:39,825
Hehehehe

465
00:38:43,495 --> 00:38:45,924
Yeah, isn't it true?

466
00:38:45,924 --> 00:38:47,759
It was really good, so give it back to me.

467
00:38:47,759 --> 00:38:50,099
No, ah... Wait a minute!

468
00:38:50,099 --> 00:38:52,330
Hey, hey, hey, hey, just ask for it yourself!

469
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:54,957
Wait, why don't you add pepper?

470
00:38:54,957 --> 00:38:56,627
It definitely tastes better with pepper

471
00:38:56,627 --> 00:38:58,297
At least it's vinegar, right?

472
00:38:58,297 --> 00:38:59,957
Well then, that's enough, no.

473
00:38:59,957 --> 00:39:01,627
Why? Well, let's have a bite.

474
00:39:01,627 --> 00:39:04,264
No, no, Mio-chan, give me another one...

475
00:39:04,264 --> 00:39:06,000
What? One more drink...

476
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:11,660
Ugh...

477
00:39:15,297 --> 00:39:17,561
You know... I won't say it.

478
00:39:17,561 --> 00:39:21,924
Wow, I feel like throwing up a little

479
00:39:21,924 --> 00:39:23,858
Oh... are you okay?

480
00:39:23,858 --> 00:39:27,660
No, can you stand it?

481
00:39:27,660 --> 00:39:32,198
Ah, I see. What about that chin?

482
00:39:32,198 --> 00:39:36,528
Next time you do something to Yume, I'll really curse you.

483
00:39:36,528 --> 00:39:41,594
I'm sorry, but I really don't want you to apologize to me.

484
00:39:41,594 --> 00:39:44,891
Sorry, Yokkoisho

485
00:39:44,891 --> 00:39:46,561
Hahahahaha

486
00:39:48,858 --> 00:39:55,924
(cell phone vibration sound)

487
00:39:57,957 --> 00:39:59,627
hello

488
00:39:59,627 --> 00:40:01,297
📱(Sakura) I didn't speak.

489
00:40:01,297 --> 00:40:05,231
Not because I forgave you, but for Taro.

490
00:40:05,231 --> 00:40:07,033
📱And that person too

491
00:40:07,033 --> 00:40:09,462
If I knew this, I would be beyond my full capacity.

492
00:40:09,462 --> 00:40:12,528
Are you seriously going to die? That's it

493
00:40:12,528 --> 00:40:16,528
📱If you want that letter back, pay 1 million yen.

494
00:40:16,528 --> 00:40:19,363
1 million is like that...

495
00:40:19,363 --> 00:40:21,429
📱(Sakura) Isn't that your parent's money?

496
00:40:21,429 --> 00:40:23,099
Huh? 📱(Sakura) Taro caught it.

497
00:40:23,099 --> 00:40:25,561
You'll be able to get it soon too, right?

498
00:40:25,561 --> 00:40:28,660
That's definitely not good, right?

499
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:31,594
📱(Sakura) I'm a good person now.

500
00:40:31,594 --> 00:40:35,528
📱If I don't pay 1 million yen, neither will my parents nor Taro.

501
00:40:35,528 --> 00:40:38,330
Then I'll give everything to that person too.

502
00:40:38,330 --> 00:40:42,627
(no sound)

503
00:40:42,627 --> 00:40:46,759
Beautiful, beautiful, not very clean haha

504
00:40:46,759 --> 00:40:49,330
⚟♬「Small sunset glow」

505
00:40:49,330 --> 00:40:52,759
It's so refreshing hahahaha

506
00:40:52,759 --> 00:40:55,165
Hahahahaha

507
00:40:55,165 --> 00:41:00,495
⚟♬〜

508
00:41:01,495 --> 00:41:03,891
Why did you ask for my sister's number?

509
00:41:05,165 --> 00:41:11,759
What does it mean when you say your sister is a criminal?

510
00:41:11,759 --> 00:41:14,957
Did you steal a million for me?

511
00:41:14,957 --> 00:41:18,231
Because I wanted to make sure, huh?

512
00:41:18,231 --> 00:41:20,858
(Sakura) It's seriously disgusting, can you please stop?

513
00:41:20,858 --> 00:41:23,594
So you thought you could date?

514
00:41:23,594 --> 00:41:25,264
Because it's a nuisance

515
00:41:30,429 --> 00:41:34,231
That's a lie.

516
00:41:40,561 --> 00:41:45,132
What really happened with my sister? Don't come to the hospital anymore

517
00:42:13,132 --> 00:42:15,957
Sigh... no...

518
00:42:15,957 --> 00:42:17,759
(Chihiro) What are you doing?

519
00:42:19,594 --> 00:42:21,957
Especially...

520
00:42:21,957 --> 00:42:24,858
(Chihiro) Is someone dead?

521
00:42:24,858 --> 00:42:26,528
Huh?

522
00:42:28,726 --> 00:42:33,924
Sigh... I thought it was kind of weird after all.

523
00:42:33,924 --> 00:42:36,858
Because something terrible happens and I need money for it.

524
00:42:36,858 --> 00:42:41,000
You came here, right? different?

525
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,957
No, like with my dad.

526
00:42:43,957 --> 00:42:45,858
Did someone die because of you?

527
00:42:45,858 --> 00:42:47,528
Are you listening?

528
00:42:47,528 --> 00:42:51,891
♬〜

529
00:42:51,891 --> 00:42:56,759
(Chihiro)《I wish it had all been a dream...》

530
00:42:56,759 --> 00:42:59,660
《That you were born》

531
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:19,660
♬〜

532
00:43:19,660 --> 00:43:21,363
♬〜

533
00:43:21,363 --> 00:43:23,033
(Kanda) Mr. Endo

534
00:43:23,033 --> 00:43:25,132
Can I have a moment? There aren't enough people

535
00:43:25,132 --> 00:43:27,561
(Endo) Huh? please

536
00:43:28,561 --> 00:43:30,858
Did you say "Come at least once"?

537
00:43:33,066 --> 00:43:35,165
(Sound of door opening) (Kayoko) Oh, sorry.

538
00:43:35,165 --> 00:43:37,198
(Endo) Ah, hello.

539
00:43:37,198 --> 00:43:40,429
(Kayoko) You're already a father.

540
00:43:40,429 --> 00:43:42,495
It's really just a little bit already

541
00:43:42,495 --> 00:43:44,594
If I took my eyes off you for a moment, you'd walk out.

542
00:43:44,594 --> 00:43:46,297
Ah, no, it's okay.

543
00:43:46,297 --> 00:43:48,924
I went out in the middle of the night the other day...

544
00:43:48,924 --> 00:43:53,594
Kairiki Moving Center Gymnast! Huh?

545
00:43:53,594 --> 00:43:57,363
Ah, the man from the couple who found me at that time.

546
00:43:57,363 --> 00:43:59,924
Because I was wearing that uniform...

547
00:43:59,924 --> 00:44:03,330
Well, I've really caused you a lot of trouble.

548
00:44:03,330 --> 00:44:05,858
Dad, please be careful too.

549
00:44:05,858 --> 00:44:17,198
♬〜

550
00:44:17,198 --> 00:44:18,858
I'm home

551
00:44:18,858 --> 00:44:31,330
♬〜

552
00:44:31,330 --> 00:44:33,000
Taro...

553
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:40,660
Mom, were you happy?

554
00:44:40,660 --> 00:44:45,099
Why couldn't you be more kind?

555
00:44:45,099 --> 00:44:48,957
(Sakura) In order to protect your friend, I lost my friend.

556
00:44:48,957 --> 00:44:53,000
I want to be friends with Mio-chan forever...
